712390f-a.title: Manhattan: 37th Street (East) - 1st Avenue
712390f-a.text:
300 to 310 E. 37th Street, at, adjourning and east of
the S. E. corner of Second Avenue (right), as viewed south
westward from: a point midway between First and Second Avenues.
Proriently shown is St. Gabriel's Roman Catholic Church
established here August 15, 1859 by the Rev. William H. Clowry.
The late Cardinal Farley, then a Monsignor, was pastor from
188d to 1902. His assistant ouring part of that time was the
subseouent Cardinal, Patrick J. Hayes. For an account of the
last Mass held here, see the New York Times of January l6, 1939.
Demolition will occur in June 1939.
January 25, 1939
Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority
